so I can take a shower.

1046
00:40:44,609 --> 00:40:45,811
Okay?

1047
00:40:45,843 --> 00:40:46,645
Yeah.

1048
00:40:47,679 --> 00:40:48,914
Okay, sure.

1049
00:41:04,462 --> 00:41:07,131
[intense music]

1050
00:41:28,618 --> 00:41:29,519
[Gabby] Michael?

1051
00:41:33,056 --> 00:41:34,290
Michael?

1052
00:41:34,324 --> 00:41:35,792
Sorry.

1053
00:41:35,825 --> 00:41:36,860
A million miles away.

1054
00:41:38,328 --> 00:41:39,763
You showered fast.

1055
00:41:39,796 --> 00:41:41,731
[Gabby] Listen, how
you treated me last night

1056
00:41:41,765 --> 00:41:42,999
was beyond inappropriate.

1057
00:41:43,032 --> 00:41:43,967
I know, I know you're right.

1058
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:45,135
Please just let me say this.

1059
00:41:52,474 --> 00:41:55,244
I know that you're beating
yourself up over this.

1060
00:41:55,277 --> 00:41:57,980
And I think that's a good thing.

1061
00:41:59,148 --> 00:42:01,383
I mean, you told
me I was gonna die.

1062
00:42:01,417 --> 00:42:04,787
I legit thought that
you were gonna kill me.

1063
00:42:04,820 --> 00:42:06,255
And I know you weren't
really in control

1064
00:42:06,288 --> 00:42:08,290
of what you're saying,
but that's not an excuse.

1065
00:42:08,323 --> 00:42:09,491
It came out of you.

1066
00:42:10,658 --> 00:42:12,093
I saw a side of the
man I love last night

1067
00:42:12,126 --> 00:42:14,529
that I thought was
capable of hurting me.

1068
00:42:15,563 --> 00:42:16,631
I almost stole your
car and left you here,

1069
00:42:16,664 --> 00:42:17,565
I was so scared.

1070
00:42:17,598 --> 00:42:19,066
Oh my God, really?

1071
00:42:19,100 --> 00:42:20,768
Yes, really.

1072
00:42:20,802 --> 00:42:22,804
I don't know, I couldn't.

1073
00:42:22,837 --> 00:42:23,671
Obviously.

1074
00:42:25,072 --> 00:42:26,307
If you really did have some
kind of psychotic break

1075
00:42:26,340 --> 00:42:27,842
I couldn't just abandon you here

1076
00:42:27,875 --> 00:42:29,444
when the phones don't even work.

1077
00:42:29,477 --> 00:42:30,745
I wouldn't blame
you if you did.

1078
00:42:30,778 --> 00:42:32,947
Good, I would have
been totally justified.

1079
00:42:32,980 --> 00:42:33,880
[Michael] You would have.

1080
00:42:33,915 --> 00:42:35,015
Totally in my rights.

1081
00:42:35,048 --> 00:42:36,149
I agree.

1082
00:42:36,183 --> 00:42:37,284
It's a lot for me
to take in too.

1083
00:42:37,317 --> 00:42:38,518
You have to take it in.

1084
00:42:38,552 --> 00:42:41,321
You have to know how
serious this was for me.

1085
00:42:41,354 --> 00:42:42,489
Trust me, I get it.

1086
00:42:42,522 --> 00:42:44,057
It's really serious for me too.

1087
00:42:45,525 --> 00:42:46,593
Then that said,

1088
00:42:48,328 --> 00:42:50,397
if you know that, I
need you to promise me

1089
00:42:50,430 --> 00:42:51,865
if anything like
this happens again,

1090
00:42:51,899 --> 00:42:54,902
you're gonna see like, a doctor.

1091
00:42:54,936 --> 00:42:56,136
Yeah, of course.

1092
00:42:56,169 --> 00:42:57,736
Of course, yeah.

1093
00:42:57,770 --> 00:43:00,206
And I think we
should put a moratorium

1094
00:43:00,239 --> 00:43:01,440
on getting stoned.

1095
00:43:03,409 --> 00:43:04,243
Absolutely.

1096
00:43:06,111 --> 00:43:06,947
All right then.

1097
00:43:08,147 --> 00:43:11,217
You're sorry and
we're in agreement.

1098
00:43:12,852 --> 00:43:13,686
So...

1099
00:43:15,922 --> 00:43:18,457
I don't think we
have to break up.

1100
00:43:19,892 --> 00:43:21,927
I really do love you, dude.

1101
00:43:23,328 --> 00:43:25,965
And I'm still upset
about everything but

1102
00:43:27,432 --> 00:43:30,268
I'm sorry for saying some
of the things I said.

1103
00:43:30,301 --> 00:43:32,470
You don't have to apologize.

1104
00:43:33,872 --> 00:43:34,706
I deserve it.

1105
00:43:43,147 --> 00:43:43,949
I love you.

1106
00:43:49,319 --> 00:43:50,621
Let's just try
and put behind us

1107
00:43:50,654 --> 00:43:52,356
for the next couple
of days, yeah?

1108
00:43:53,590 --> 00:43:54,424
Yeah.

1109
00:43:55,526 --> 00:43:56,693
Gladly.

1110
00:43:56,727 --> 00:43:58,228
[ball clacking]

1111
00:43:58,262 --> 00:43:59,998
Woo, game!

1112
00:44:00,030 --> 00:44:00,797
Best two out of three?

1113
00:44:00,831 --> 00:44:02,266
No, it's cool.

1114
00:44:02,299 --> 00:44:03,734
I'm fine with you just being
better at this one than me.

1115
00:44:03,767 --> 00:44:05,168
Okay, okay, let's
play darts then.

1116
00:44:05,202 --> 00:44:06,470
Here, I'm lousy at those.

1117
00:44:10,506 --> 00:44:11,340
Here.

1118
00:44:18,347 --> 00:44:19,248
Okay.

1119
00:44:19,282 --> 00:44:20,216
Hang on, let me show you.

1120
00:44:20,249 --> 00:44:21,083
Here.

1121
00:44:22,019 --> 00:44:23,419
All right.

1122
00:44:23,452 --> 00:44:24,287
Take that.

1123
00:44:25,621 --> 00:44:26,822
All right, just keep your
eye on where you're aiming

1124
00:44:26,856 --> 00:44:27,790
and your brain will
fill in the rest.

1125
00:44:27,823 --> 00:44:29,026
- Okay?
- You know what?

1126
00:44:29,058 --> 00:44:30,693
I don't think I'm very
good at this one either.

1127
00:44:30,726 --> 00:44:32,562
Why don't we just take
it easy on the couch,

1128
00:44:32,595 --> 00:44:33,429
watch a movie?

1129
00:44:35,063 --> 00:44:36,131
Okay, yeah.

1130
00:44:40,235 --> 00:44:41,069
Hey, hey.

1131
00:44:44,072 --> 00:44:45,774
I love you, you know?

1132
00:44:45,807 --> 00:44:46,641
I know.

1133
00:44:49,946 --> 00:44:51,179
I love you too.

1134
00:45:09,630 --> 00:45:11,799
You know, I could
use a drink actually.

1135
00:45:11,832 --> 00:45:13,034
You want one?

1136
00:45:14,401 --> 00:45:15,202
Yeah.

1137
00:45:16,203 --> 00:45:17,438
Seven and seven?

1138
00:45:36,289 --> 00:45:39,225
[glasses clinking]

1139
00:45:52,939 --> 00:45:54,974
[Gabby sobbing]

1140
00:45:55,008 --> 00:45:57,376
[Man On TV] Extra
daylight does us.

1141
00:45:57,409 --> 00:45:59,378
Now we've still got a
three hour drive back.

1142
00:45:59,411 --> 00:46:01,446
We're not going to be
home until after midnight.

1143
00:46:01,480 --> 00:46:02,781
[Woman On TV] Well if
it really bugs you, Johnny

1144
00:46:02,814 --> 00:46:04,083
you wouldn't do it.

1145
00:46:04,117 --> 00:46:05,350
[Johnny] You think
I wanna blow Sunday

1146
00:46:05,384 --> 00:46:07,053
on a scene like this?

1147
00:46:07,086 --> 00:46:08,854
[Man On TV] You know, I figure
we're either going to have

1148
00:46:08,887 --> 00:46:10,621
to move mother out
here or move to Grays.

1149
00:46:10,655 --> 00:46:11,856
I broke us, didn't I?

1150
00:46:11,890 --> 00:46:13,357
[Woman On TV] He can't
make a trip like this.

1151
00:46:13,391 --> 00:46:14,225
No.

1152
00:46:15,760 --> 00:46:16,827
I don't think so.

1153
00:46:18,429 --> 00:46:19,630
I don't know.

1154
00:46:19,664 --> 00:46:21,265
I just don't feel
quite right yet.

1155
00:46:23,267 --> 00:46:24,635
That's okay, isn't it?

1156
00:46:24,669 --> 00:46:29,674
Yeah, that's okay, I get it.

1157
00:46:32,677 --> 00:46:33,643
I was thinking.

1158
00:46:36,646 --> 00:46:39,549
Maybe this weekend just got a
little too weird to salvage.

1159
00:46:41,184 --> 00:46:44,922
Maybe we should just go home
and try again another time.

1160
00:46:44,955 --> 00:46:46,957
Is that what you want?

1161
00:46:49,927 --> 00:46:50,827
Yeah, okay.

1162
00:46:52,429 --> 00:46:55,198
Okay, then let's
go pack the car.

1163
00:47:01,303 --> 00:47:03,772
[eerie music]

1164
00:47:36,304 --> 00:47:37,605
Sure about this?

1165
00:47:37,638 --> 00:47:39,474
I don't want to break up.

1166
00:47:39,507 --> 00:47:42,243
I just don't think I'm
going to feel okay enough

1167
00:47:42,276 --> 00:47:43,979
to have a good
time this weekend.

1168
00:47:44,012 --> 00:47:44,846
Yeah, sure.

1169
00:47:45,947 --> 00:47:46,780
Thanks.

1170
00:47:52,419 --> 00:47:53,687
Driving out of here
doesn't change anything

1171
00:47:53,720 --> 00:47:55,156
we've talked about.

1172
00:47:55,189 --> 00:47:56,958
[somber piano music]

1173
00:47:56,991 --> 00:47:58,358
You mean about us or what?

1174
00:47:58,391 --> 00:47:59,994
About us.

1175
00:48:00,027 --> 00:48:00,861
About you.

1176
00:48:02,529 --> 00:48:03,931
Leaving the cabin

1177
00:48:03,965 --> 00:48:06,100
doesn't mean you're driving
away from your death.

1178
00:48:06,134 --> 00:48:06,968
Micheal.

1179
00:48:10,336 --> 00:48:12,239
I thought we were
done with this.

1180
00:48:12,271 --> 00:48:13,439
What have I said to
give you the impression

1181
00:48:13,472 --> 00:48:14,273
that we were done with this?

1182
00:48:14,306 --> 00:48:16,109
Not you, Michael.

1183
00:48:16,143 --> 00:48:17,443
I was hoping since
we were both sober,

1184
00:48:17,476 --> 00:48:18,344
this wouldn't happen again.

1185
00:48:18,377 --> 00:48:19,578
That would make sense

1186
00:48:19,612 --> 00:48:21,514
if this was caused
by not being sober.

1187
00:48:22,715 --> 00:48:25,952
I just want to be in
my own bed by myself.

1188
00:48:25,986 --> 00:48:27,353
I want to go home.

1189
00:48:27,386 --> 00:48:29,355
Home is with me, Gabrielle.

1190
00:48:29,388 --> 00:48:30,723
You need to understand that.

1191
00:48:30,756 --> 00:48:34,093
You want comfort,
you want security.

1192
00:48:34,126 --> 00:48:36,394
I'm the source of
all of those things.

1193
00:48:38,463 --> 00:48:39,564
I know you want me.

1194
00:48:40,431 --> 00:48:41,432
You love me.

1195
00:48:42,634 --> 00:48:44,036
All you have to do
is recognize me.

1196
00:48:44,069 --> 00:48:45,503
I can't do this right now.

1197
00:48:45,537 --> 00:48:47,572
Bring Michael back,
I want to go home!

1198
00:48:47,605 --> 00:48:49,340
That's where I'm
trying to take you.

1199
00:48:49,374 --> 00:48:50,408
So come!

1200
00:48:50,441 --> 00:48:52,443
Come to the source of all joy,

1201
00:48:52,477 --> 00:48:54,280
of all novelty and humor,

1202
00:48:54,312 --> 00:48:55,880
of all rest and contentedness,

1203
00:48:55,915 --> 00:48:59,316
come to the source of
all kinship and life.

1204
00:49:00,218 --> 00:49:01,552
Come to the spirit of God!

1205
00:49:04,289 --> 00:49:05,123
Yes.

1206
00:49:06,757 --> 00:49:09,194
I'm only here because our
hearts long for each other.

1207
00:49:09,227 --> 00:49:10,261
If you drive away
from this place

1208
00:49:10,295 --> 00:49:12,462
where I have
approached you plainly,

1209
00:49:12,496 --> 00:49:14,232
you're driving away
from your Lord.

1210
00:49:15,599 --> 00:49:16,767
You're making a choice.

1211
00:49:17,835 --> 00:49:21,838
But since this decision
is irreversible,

1212
00:49:21,871 --> 00:49:23,873
you need to know what
that truly means.

1213
00:49:23,907 --> 00:49:25,708
You have a misconception
about hell.

1214
00:49:27,177 --> 00:49:30,680
It's not a punishment,
it's a consequence.

1215
00:49:32,282 --> 00:49:34,550
In this life you
are a small rowboat,

1216
00:49:34,584 --> 00:49:36,786
adrift in the ocean
without a map.

1217
00:49:36,819 --> 00:49:38,721
I'm an ocean liner
pulling up alongside you

1218
00:49:38,754 --> 00:49:41,424
and telling you I'm headed
where you need to go.

1219
00:49:42,326 --> 00:49:43,227
You have a choice.

1220
00:49:44,660 --> 00:49:46,929
Either hit your boat to mine
and let me take you there

1221
00:49:48,097 --> 00:49:50,099
or push off from
me and drift away.

1222
00:49:51,466 --> 00:49:53,135
Life may be temporary, but you,

1223
00:49:53,169 --> 00:49:55,204
you, Gabrielle are eternal,

1224
00:49:55,238 --> 00:49:56,805
made in my eternal image.

1225
00:49:57,940 --> 00:49:59,976
Do you understand what happens

1226
00:50:00,009 --> 00:50:01,110
if you push yourself off from me

1227
00:50:01,143 --> 00:50:02,444
and all that I am?

1228
00:50:03,612 --> 00:50:04,813
The most gentle push
away from my ship

1229
00:50:04,846 --> 00:50:06,615
may not get you very far
after just a few hours

1230
00:50:06,648 --> 00:50:07,649
or even a few days,

1231
00:50:07,682 --> 00:50:08,783
but over eternity?

1232
00:50:10,417 --> 00:50:14,022
Infinitely far and farther yet.

1233
00:50:14,055 --> 00:50:15,357
If you choose to
rid yourself of me

1234
00:50:15,389 --> 00:50:18,459
you'll lose all of me.

1235
00:50:18,492 --> 00:50:21,263
That fear you have now,
the cornered feeling.

1236
00:50:23,064 --> 00:50:25,267
You still have hope this way.

1237
00:50:25,300 --> 00:50:27,335
Think of how you'll
feel on your first step

1238
00:50:27,369 --> 00:50:29,737
of that internal walk into hell.

1239
00:50:29,770 --> 00:50:34,074
The fear, the desperation
with no hope of reversal,

1240
00:50:34,108 --> 00:50:36,277
only the certainty that
the terror and anguish

1241
00:50:36,310 --> 00:50:37,810
will become worse.

1242
00:50:37,844 --> 00:50:39,545
Can you feel the weight
of that on your shoulders?

1243
00:50:39,579 --> 00:50:42,216
Can you see why I've
come to plead with you?

1244
00:50:43,416 --> 00:50:45,319
It breaks my heart to
offer you everything

1245
00:50:45,352 --> 00:50:48,322
and see you requesting an
inheritance of darkness.

1246
00:50:48,355 --> 00:50:50,690
I need you to grasp this.

1247
00:50:52,059 --> 00:50:54,895
You will be denying
the divine image

1248
00:50:54,929 --> 00:50:56,130
that I have placed within you

1249
00:50:56,163 --> 00:50:58,530
that separates you
from any other animal.

1250
00:50:58,563 --> 00:51:00,465
You will feel only
the primal fear

1251
00:51:00,499 --> 00:51:01,667
of being prey.

1252
00:51:02,567 --> 00:51:03,669
As your Creator,

1253
00:51:07,006 --> 00:51:08,740
your father,

1254
00:51:08,774 --> 00:51:10,944
do you think I want to see
you drift to the everlasting

1255
00:51:10,977 --> 00:51:14,347
knowing that with
every moment of agony,

1256
00:51:15,747 --> 00:51:18,418
every gnash of your
teeth, every hunger pang,

1257
00:51:18,450 --> 00:51:21,386
every shallow gasp
for toxic air,

1258
00:51:21,420 --> 00:51:23,587
every yearn for a drop of water,

1259
00:51:23,621 --> 00:51:25,856
every longing for even another
soul to commiserate with,

1260
00:51:25,891 --> 00:51:29,794
that you are no closer to
any semblance of relief?

1261
00:51:29,827 --> 00:51:32,097
Imagine living a
trillion trillion years

1262
00:51:32,130 --> 00:51:35,633
and being no closer
than when you got there.

1263
00:51:35,666 --> 00:51:37,302
The remorse that you
could have avoided it all

1264
00:51:37,336 --> 00:51:39,171
with one conversation,

1265
00:51:39,204 --> 00:51:42,274
this conversation, never leaves.

1266
00:51:43,708 --> 00:51:45,742
If you drive away
from this cabin,

1267
00:51:45,775 --> 00:51:47,144
you're driving away from me.

1268
00:51:48,279 --> 00:51:51,315
And directly, directly
into this fate.

1269
00:51:52,283 --> 00:51:53,683
I've come to rescue you.

1270
00:51:54,751 --> 00:51:56,753
I've come here to save you!

1271
00:51:56,786 --> 00:51:58,389
I've come here
because I love you.

1272
00:51:58,422 --> 00:52:00,358
I made you.

1273
00:52:00,391 --> 00:52:04,728
I made you specifically
from nothing

1274
00:52:06,197 --> 00:52:07,898
because you offer the
universe something

1275
00:52:07,932 --> 00:52:09,698
no other soul is able to.

1276
00:52:09,732 --> 00:52:12,701
Losing you is worse than a
parent losing their child.

1277
00:52:14,137 --> 00:52:16,206
I want you in hell far less
than you want to be there

1278
00:52:16,239 --> 00:52:19,209
but I do not drag people kicking
and screaming into heaven.

1279
00:52:20,609 --> 00:52:22,078
Paradise is an opt-in system.

1280
00:52:23,413 --> 00:52:25,482
And you opt in by
placing your trust in me,

1281
00:52:26,849 --> 00:52:28,218
hitching your boat to mine.

1282
00:52:29,386 --> 00:52:31,121
It's free, it's right
there for the taking

1283
00:52:31,154 --> 00:52:32,922
if you just take it.

1284
00:52:35,190 --> 00:52:38,526
I've implored you, but
I will not demand you.

1285
00:52:39,594 --> 00:52:41,997
It is and must be your choice.

1286
00:52:43,698 --> 00:52:46,268
And we'll both live eternally
with the consequences.

1287
00:52:46,301 --> 00:52:47,903
Why are you doing this to me?

1288
00:52:47,936 --> 00:52:49,338
This is not to terrify you.

1289
00:52:49,371 --> 00:52:51,006
Though I know it does.

1290
00:52:51,040 --> 00:52:52,207
We find ourselves in an airplane

1291
00:52:52,241 --> 00:52:53,674
that I know is going to crash,

1292
00:52:53,708 --> 00:52:55,576
and I'm begging you
to put on a parachute,

1293
00:52:55,610 --> 00:52:57,512
but you don't
believe you need one!

1294
00:52:57,544 --> 00:52:58,845
The most merciful thing
that I can do right now

1295
00:52:58,880 --> 00:53:00,781
is hanging by your legs
outside of the plane

1296
00:53:00,814 --> 00:53:02,283
and show you the
drop you're facing.

1297
00:53:02,316 --> 00:53:04,485
Maybe then, you'll see why
you need the parachute.

1298
00:53:04,519 --> 00:53:05,685
Everything I've told you

1299
00:53:05,719 --> 00:53:07,788
is what you get without me.

1300
00:53:07,821 --> 00:53:10,992
Not desiring hell is enough
to know you desire heaven.

1301
00:53:11,025 --> 00:53:14,529
And desiring heaven is enough
to know that you desire me.

1302
00:53:15,862 --> 00:53:17,098
If you're terrified
by the thought of hell

1303
00:53:17,131 --> 00:53:19,467
then you and I are
on the same team.

1304
00:53:20,700 --> 00:53:22,768
It is that simple.

1305
00:53:22,802 --> 00:53:24,304
I hate this!

1306
00:53:24,337 --> 00:53:25,838
What's the loving thing to do

1307
00:53:25,872 --> 00:53:28,375
when someone's denying their
own self-destructive behavior?

1308
00:53:30,477 --> 00:53:34,647
Doesn't an intervention
provide help for an alcoholic?

1309
00:53:36,516 --> 00:53:39,119
No matter if it's
personally difficult?

1310
00:53:40,653 --> 00:53:45,157
Or is that too
personal of a metaphor?

1311
00:53:45,191 --> 00:53:46,825
I know the guilt
hasn't left you.

1312
00:53:48,494 --> 00:53:50,695
Doubt can serve you or you it.

1313
00:53:50,728 --> 00:53:51,897
And look where doubt got you

1314
00:53:51,931 --> 00:53:54,133
in your mother's
final days on earth.

1315
00:53:55,301 --> 00:53:57,303
It's sending you into
even worse fate now.

1316
00:53:58,803 --> 00:54:01,874
You want knowledge, but this
just isn't a knowledge test.

1317
00:54:01,907 --> 00:54:03,542
My own know me.

1318
00:54:05,878 --> 00:54:07,379
You know who I am, Gabrielle.

1319
00:54:09,680 --> 00:54:11,015
I just need you to say it.

1320
00:54:12,649 --> 00:54:13,684
Who am I, Gabrielle?

1321
00:54:15,086 --> 00:54:16,454
We both know that
you know the answer.

1322
00:54:16,488 --> 00:54:18,622
Please tell me, who am I?

1323
00:54:24,129 --> 00:54:26,331
There's nothing
left to say, than.

1324
00:54:26,364 --> 00:54:29,633
I have loved you
from eternity past

1325
00:54:29,666 --> 00:54:32,636
and I will mourn you
into eternity future.

1326
00:54:34,037 --> 00:54:35,139
Goodbye, my Gabrielle.

1327
00:54:41,912 --> 00:54:43,013
[Michael] It's okay.

1328
00:54:44,515 --> 00:54:45,949
I'll have you home
in like six hours,

1329
00:54:45,983 --> 00:54:49,186
and don't worry about
calling me or anything

1330
00:54:49,219 --> 00:54:50,154
until you're ready.

1331
00:54:55,225 --> 00:54:56,627
What?

1332
00:54:56,659 --> 00:54:58,660
[clears throat] What's wrong?

1333
00:54:58,693 --> 00:54:59,595
Did I do it again?

1334
00:55:00,630 --> 00:55:02,697
Gabby?

1335
00:55:02,731 --> 00:55:05,134
Oh my god.

1336
00:55:05,168 --> 00:55:07,669
Gabby, I thought this
was drugs or whatever

1337
00:55:07,702 --> 00:55:09,639
but if this has happened...

1338
00:55:09,671 --> 00:55:11,340
I'm completely sober right now.

1339
00:55:13,075 --> 00:55:15,011
You have to take me home.

1340
00:55:15,044 --> 00:55:16,345
I need help.

1341
00:55:16,379 --> 00:55:18,247
- I really need help.
- I'm so scared.

1342
00:55:18,281 --> 00:55:19,182
It's okay, it's okay.

1343
00:55:19,215 --> 00:55:21,116
Baby, look at me, look at me.

1344
00:55:21,149 --> 00:55:23,051
It's me, I'm back.

1345
00:55:23,084 --> 00:55:24,452
No, I don't want
you back right now.

1346
00:55:24,486 --> 00:55:25,320
I want him back.

1347
00:55:25,353 --> 00:55:26,521
Him?

1348
00:55:26,555 --> 00:55:27,755
Babe there's no him,
are you serious?

1349
00:55:27,788 --> 00:55:29,424
- It's me.
- How do you know that?

1350
00:55:30,525 --> 00:55:31,993
Some of the things he said,

1351
00:55:32,027 --> 00:55:33,128
I just can't imagine them
coming from your brain.

1352
00:55:33,161 --> 00:55:34,229
[Michael] But they
came out of my mouth.

1353
00:55:34,262 --> 00:55:34,930
Yeah, exactly!

1354
00:55:36,264 --> 00:55:37,566
And he knew things.

1355
00:55:38,867 --> 00:55:40,101
Michael, he knew
something about my mother

1356
00:55:40,135 --> 00:55:40,936
that I never told you.

1357
00:55:40,969 --> 00:55:41,769
That's not possible.

1358
00:55:41,802 --> 00:55:43,238
That's not possible.

1359
00:55:43,271 --> 00:55:46,173
No, he said he knew
that I had the opportunity

1360
00:55:46,207 --> 00:55:48,342
to stage an
intervention for her,

1361
00:55:48,375 --> 00:55:49,809
and I didn't.

1362
00:55:49,842 --> 00:55:53,080
And I have to think if she
still had her health insurance

1363
00:55:53,113 --> 00:55:54,682
when she got sick, she would...

1364
00:55:55,782 --> 00:55:56,716
He knew how guilty

1365
00:55:56,749 --> 00:55:57,985
- I still feel.
- He said that?

1366
00:55:58,018 --> 00:55:59,220
He said that, he told
you that specifically?

1367
00:55:59,253 --> 00:56:01,088
He said that this was
like an intervention.

1368
00:56:01,121 --> 00:56:02,656
And he knew my guilt.

1369
00:56:02,690 --> 00:56:03,856
And then he mentioned my mom.

1370
00:56:03,891 --> 00:56:07,094
That's not the same
thing as knowing.

1371
00:56:07,127 --> 00:56:09,462
Your own guilt is forcing you
to connect a bunch of dots

1372
00:56:09,495 --> 00:56:10,363
that aren't really there.

1373
00:56:10,396 --> 00:56:11,464
You don't know that.

1374
00:56:11,497 --> 00:56:12,831
I want to talk to God again.

1375
00:56:12,865 --> 00:56:13,933
Make him come back!

1376
00:56:13,967 --> 00:56:15,435
Make him come back!

1377
00:56:15,468 --> 00:56:19,505
Stop making the breakdown
that I'm having about you.

1378
00:56:19,539 --> 00:56:21,007
You're not the one
in danger here.

1379
00:56:21,040 --> 00:56:23,676
My brain is breaking, okay?

1380
00:56:24,544 --> 00:56:26,112
We have to go home.

1381
00:56:26,145 --> 00:56:26,946
I'm not driving like this.

1382
00:56:26,980 --> 00:56:28,448
I can't do that.

1383
00:56:28,481 --> 00:56:31,750
We're in an emergency
situation here, all right?

1384
00:56:31,783 --> 00:56:33,385
You need to be brave.

1385
00:56:33,418 --> 00:56:35,254
What if I have another
episode while I'm driving?

1386
00:56:35,287 --> 00:56:36,488
I could hurt us or worse.

1387
00:56:36,521 --> 00:56:38,056
I'm not driving right now!

1388
00:56:38,090 --> 00:56:39,091
You have to!

1389
00:56:40,058 --> 00:56:42,261
No, he told me that if I left

1390
00:56:42,294 --> 00:56:43,462
he would accept
that as my answer.

1391
00:56:43,495 --> 00:56:45,097
I would be going to hell!

1392
00:56:45,130 --> 00:56:46,565
He didn't say anything!

1393
00:56:46,598 --> 00:56:48,166
It's me.

1394
00:56:48,200 --> 00:56:50,102
You're not dying, you're
not going to hell.

1395
00:56:50,135 --> 00:56:52,537
I said those things
because I am sick.

1396
00:56:53,771 --> 00:56:54,940
Here, take these keys.

1397
00:56:54,973 --> 00:56:56,974
Take these keys from
me, switch seats with me

1398
00:56:57,008 --> 00:56:58,009
and drive us home.

1399
00:56:59,410 --> 00:57:01,412
Please, this is life
or death, Gabrielle.

1400
00:57:03,714 --> 00:57:05,182
Why did you call me Gabrielle?

1401
00:57:05,216 --> 00:57:07,151
Because it's your name.

1402
00:57:07,184 --> 00:57:09,220
You never call me Gabrielle.

1403
00:57:09,253 --> 00:57:11,122
Take the keys.

1404
00:57:11,155 --> 00:57:12,990
Come on, this could be
seizures for all we know!

1405
00:57:13,024 --> 00:57:15,960
Baby, we can't afford
to waste our time.

1406
00:57:15,993 --> 00:57:17,361
Please, please.

1407
00:57:38,814 --> 00:57:42,385
[intense electronic music]

1408
00:58:25,393 --> 00:58:26,227
Okay.

1409
00:58:28,329 --> 00:58:29,163
God?

1410
00:58:30,631 --> 00:58:32,500
Please come back.

1411
00:58:32,533 --> 00:58:33,934
I need to talk to you again.

1412
00:58:37,270 --> 00:58:38,105
Please?

1413
00:58:39,272 --> 00:58:40,474
I'm open, I promise.

1414
00:58:40,507 --> 00:58:41,942
I just have some questions

1415
00:58:41,975 --> 00:58:43,677
and I want to get to the
bottom of what's happening.

1416
00:58:43,710 --> 00:58:45,078
It's no use, Gabby.

1417
00:58:45,112 --> 00:58:46,012
This doesn't concern you.

1418
00:58:46,046 --> 00:58:47,114
This is between me and him.

1419
00:58:47,147 --> 00:58:48,248
It wasn't God that
was talking to you.

1420
00:58:48,281 --> 00:58:49,249
That was me.

1421
00:58:49,282 --> 00:58:50,350
You need to get that

1422
00:58:50,384 --> 00:58:51,451
- through your head.
- How would you know that?

1423
00:58:51,485 --> 00:58:52,119
You weren't there.

1424
00:58:53,353 --> 00:58:56,022
Please, God, talk to me
through Michael again.

1425
00:58:58,290 --> 00:58:59,392
Why don't we black
out the windows

1426
00:58:59,425 --> 00:59:00,659
or light some candles

1427
00:59:00,693 --> 00:59:01,627
- or something?
- It's not a seance, dude.

1428
00:59:01,660 --> 00:59:02,361
Then what are we doing?

1429
00:59:02,395 --> 00:59:02,995
I don't know.

1430
00:59:03,028 --> 00:59:03,829
Prayer, I guess?

1431
00:59:05,731 --> 00:59:06,532
Prayer?

1432
00:59:06,565 --> 00:59:07,666
Yeah, prayer.

1433
00:59:13,139 --> 00:59:14,306
[gentle piano music]

1434
00:59:14,340 --> 00:59:15,174
Prayer.

1435
00:59:23,548 --> 00:59:24,382
Dear God.

1436
00:59:26,851 --> 00:59:29,287
If there is a God, I know
you can hear me right now.

1437
00:59:30,455 --> 00:59:32,257
I don't know what's
going on with Michael.

1438
00:59:32,290 --> 00:59:33,291
I just don't.

1439
00:59:34,959 --> 00:59:38,396
But if I do have a creator

1440
00:59:38,430 --> 00:59:41,566
and if I have any
obligation to you,

1441
00:59:43,067 --> 00:59:43,903
I want to know.

1442
00:59:45,436 --> 00:59:47,404
And if I'm in a
dangerous situation

1443
00:59:47,438 --> 00:59:48,405
and you can get me out of it,

1444
00:59:48,439 --> 00:59:51,041
then I need your help.

1445
00:59:54,144 --> 00:59:57,548
I'm little and you are big.

1446
01:00:02,252 --> 01:00:04,321
I'm confused and scared and

1447
01:00:05,489 --> 01:00:07,257
I don't even know what
I need or want right now

1448
01:00:07,291 --> 01:00:08,892
but you do.

1449
01:00:08,926 --> 01:00:12,628
So please, anything.

1450
01:00:16,900 --> 01:00:18,367
Don't abandon me here.

1451
01:00:21,637 --> 01:00:22,472
Shit.

1452
01:00:25,608 --> 01:00:26,776
Did anything happen?

1453
01:00:26,809 --> 01:00:28,311
Did I do it again?

1454
01:00:29,278 --> 01:00:30,146
You see?

1455
01:00:31,047 --> 01:00:33,081
See, it's not real.

1456
01:00:34,282 --> 01:00:35,952
If God was talking
to you through me,

1457
01:00:37,819 --> 01:00:38,587
why wouldn't he answer that?

1458
01:00:38,620 --> 01:00:39,788
I don't know.

1459
01:00:40,722 --> 01:00:41,958
Maybe it's too late.

1460
01:00:41,990 --> 01:00:44,426
Maybe the car is my last
chance and I blew it.

1461
01:00:46,761 --> 01:00:47,930
Maybe I'm damned.

1462
01:00:49,464 --> 01:00:50,732
Let's just go home.

1463
01:00:50,765 --> 01:00:52,100
This is all going to be
a bad memory, all right?

1464
01:00:52,133 --> 01:00:53,301
No, if this is
really happening,

1465
01:00:53,335 --> 01:00:55,337
then driving home finalizes it.

1466
01:00:55,370 --> 01:00:57,137
As long as we're
here, there's hope.

1467
01:01:00,474 --> 01:01:02,376
Okay.

1468
01:01:02,409 --> 01:01:03,244
Okay.

1469
01:01:04,578 --> 01:01:06,647
I'm gonna make you some dinner.

1470
01:01:06,680 --> 01:01:08,449
You barely ate today.

1471
01:01:41,214 --> 01:01:42,048
I love you.

1472
01:01:43,216 --> 01:01:45,250
Don't forget that, okay?

1473
01:01:45,284 --> 01:01:46,084
Yeah.

1474
01:01:47,052 --> 01:01:47,854
I love you too.

1475
01:01:49,755 --> 01:01:51,557
Probably won't be
the most exciting part

1476
01:01:51,590 --> 01:01:53,292
of the weekend anymore, but

1477
01:01:54,459 --> 01:01:56,628
this does happen
to be my specialty.

1478
01:01:58,330 --> 01:01:59,565
Try to eat something.

1479
01:01:59,598 --> 01:02:00,799
You need it.

1480
01:02:00,832 --> 01:02:03,235
And it's delicious if
I may say so myself.

1481
01:02:06,705 --> 01:02:08,539
Come on, it's not
that horrid, is it?

1482
01:02:09,840 --> 01:02:10,675
No.

1483
01:02:12,143 --> 01:02:14,679
It just occurred to me that
this could be my last meal.

1484
01:02:17,916 --> 01:02:19,083
Am I going crazy?

1485
01:02:20,484 --> 01:02:22,520
I hate seeing you like this.

1486
01:02:22,553 --> 01:02:23,821
Look where you are.

1487
01:02:23,855 --> 01:02:25,356
Here with me, okay?

1488
01:02:25,389 --> 01:02:26,858
You're safe here.

1489
01:02:26,892 --> 01:02:28,559
I'm not going to let
anything hurt you.

1490
01:02:28,593 --> 01:02:31,596
We could crash driving home
on Sunday for all I know.

1491
01:02:31,629 --> 01:02:34,497
Let's call off work
and go back on Monday.

1492
01:02:34,531 --> 01:02:36,399
I won't let anything
happen to you.

1493
01:02:36,433 --> 01:02:37,300
I promise.

1494
01:02:38,201 --> 01:02:39,036
You're sweet.

1495
01:02:40,203 --> 01:02:42,439
You are, but this
is bigger than you.

1496
01:02:42,472 --> 01:02:44,341
It really isn't.

1497
01:02:44,374 --> 01:02:46,043
It is me.

1498
01:02:46,077 --> 01:02:48,244
I'm the one who put
this fear in to you.

1499
01:02:48,278 --> 01:02:49,546
Okay, I find it
more concerning

1500
01:02:49,579 --> 01:02:51,114
that you're fighting
so hard to tell me

1501
01:02:51,147 --> 01:02:53,050
that nothing's really happening.

1502
01:02:53,084 --> 01:02:54,551
You know, if you
were screwing with me

1503
01:02:54,584 --> 01:02:56,785
you'd just let me believe it.

1504
01:02:56,819 --> 01:02:58,088
All the more likely
option that I have

1505
01:02:58,120 --> 01:03:00,056
some sort of psychosis.

1506
01:03:00,090 --> 01:03:01,523
Yeah, well then your psychosis

1507
01:03:01,557 --> 01:03:03,726
does a really fucking
convincing God impression.

1508
01:03:08,163 --> 01:03:09,398
Okay.

1509
01:03:09,431 --> 01:03:10,499
I know you're scared,

1510
01:03:11,800 --> 01:03:15,204
but right now there is
nothing scary happening.

1511
01:03:15,237 --> 01:03:17,941
Right now, we are a
boyfriend and a girlfriend

1512
01:03:17,974 --> 01:03:20,541
sitting down to
have a nice romantic

1513
01:03:20,575 --> 01:03:22,111
home cooked dinner together.

1514
01:03:23,778 --> 01:03:25,346
Don't worry about anything else.

1515
01:03:25,380 --> 01:03:28,249
Let's just sit here and
enjoy each other's company.

1516
01:03:28,282 --> 01:03:30,953
I don't know where I'm going
to be this time tomorrow.

1517
01:03:30,986 --> 01:03:33,122
There is a wide range
of possibilities

1518
01:03:33,154 --> 01:03:35,256
and one of them is in hell.

1519
01:03:36,457 --> 01:03:38,127
How can you expect me to
get that out of my mind?

1520
01:03:38,159 --> 01:03:40,528
Because it doesn't make
any sense to believe that.

1521
01:03:40,561 --> 01:03:42,230
God doesn't use
people as puppets.

1522
01:03:42,263 --> 01:03:44,331
Okay well if he did,
would the puppet know?

1523
01:03:44,364 --> 01:03:45,499
We can't know for certain

1524
01:03:45,532 --> 01:03:46,500
and that means that
there is a chance

1525
01:03:46,533 --> 01:03:48,102
that my clock is ticking.

1526
01:03:49,269 --> 01:03:51,738
I'm so sorry that
I've done this to you.

1527
01:03:51,772 --> 01:03:54,574
I think we're both gonna
need therapy after this.

1528
01:03:54,608 --> 01:03:56,176
Yeah, if there
is an after this.

1529
01:04:00,814 --> 01:04:01,748
You like the wine?

1530
01:04:04,418 --> 01:04:05,285
Yeah? Me too.

1531
01:04:11,190 --> 01:04:12,625
1989 Malbec.

1532
01:04:13,960 --> 01:04:15,728
Bottled in Napa Valley.

1533
01:04:18,531 --> 01:04:21,101
You ever wonder if they
just put random dates

1534
01:04:21,134 --> 01:04:22,601
on these things?

1535
01:04:22,635 --> 01:04:24,303
Yeah how do you know
it was bottled in 1989,

1536
01:04:24,336 --> 01:04:25,504
not like 2009?

1537
01:04:27,007 --> 01:04:28,541
You think you can
tell a difference?

1538
01:04:29,508 --> 01:04:31,210
Nope, I guess not.

1539
01:04:31,243 --> 01:04:32,912
And Napa Valley.

1540
01:04:34,046 --> 01:04:35,613
That's kind of
obvious, isn't it?

1541
01:04:37,883 --> 01:04:40,385
If I was going to make up where
my fraudulent wine came from

1542
01:04:40,418 --> 01:04:41,586
I would say Napa Valley.

1543
01:04:41,619 --> 01:04:43,455
It's like an
archetypical wine place.

1544
01:04:44,622 --> 01:04:46,558
Hmm, even a bit
of a cliche right?

1545
01:04:46,591 --> 01:04:48,060
Okay.

1546
01:04:48,094 --> 01:04:51,696
I appreciate you trying
to take my mind off this.

1547
01:04:52,764 --> 01:04:53,832
But please stop.

1548
01:04:54,967 --> 01:04:57,035
I just want some silence
for a minute, okay.

1549
01:04:57,068 --> 01:04:58,535
Just food for thought.

1550
01:05:03,875 --> 01:05:06,810
Think this stuff could be
a bootleg bathtub wine?

1551
01:05:06,845 --> 01:05:08,545
I'm not worried about it.

1552
01:05:08,579 --> 01:05:10,781
I'm sure there is some
kind of regulation in place

1553
01:05:10,814 --> 01:05:12,917
that keeps people
from just lying

1554
01:05:12,951 --> 01:05:15,586
about what they're
selling like that, okay?

1555
01:05:15,619 --> 01:05:16,420
Yeah.

1556
01:05:19,124 --> 01:05:20,623
You're sure about that though?

1557
01:05:21,724 --> 01:05:22,725
How are you so sure?

1558
01:05:24,393 --> 01:05:25,661
What do you mean?

1559
01:05:25,695 --> 01:05:28,165
You said I'm sure there is,

1560
01:05:28,198 --> 01:05:30,000
not, maybe there is.

1561
01:05:31,834 --> 01:05:33,036
