among evil and injustice.

1844
01:17:54,780 --> 01:17:56,148
Your soul wants perfection.

1845
01:17:57,349 --> 01:17:58,550
Your soul wants me.

1846
01:17:58,584 --> 01:17:59,985
Yeah but you created
it, you made the world.

1847
01:18:00,018 --> 01:18:00,854
I did.

1848
01:18:02,421 --> 01:18:03,622
But that doesn't mean

1849
01:18:03,655 --> 01:18:05,657
that I like everything
that happens in it.

1850
01:18:05,691 --> 01:18:07,025
These things you're
highlighting are things

1851
01:18:07,059 --> 01:18:08,426
that grieve me as well.

1852
01:18:09,895 --> 01:18:12,597
I yearn for justice.

1853
01:18:13,764 --> 01:18:15,700
I mourn for those in
hell the same as you.

1854
01:18:17,101 --> 01:18:19,337
I gave humanity this world,

1855
01:18:19,370 --> 01:18:20,939
but I did not create
the evil in it.

1856
01:18:20,973 --> 01:18:23,040
You did, all of you.

1857
01:18:23,074 --> 01:18:24,542
Unlike some faulty hardware,

1858
01:18:24,575 --> 01:18:28,679
you are a moral agent
with a free will.

1859
01:18:28,713 --> 01:18:32,182
Humanity chose evil voluntarily.

1860
01:18:34,184 --> 01:18:37,087
Allow me to properly refocus
your righteous anger.

1861
01:18:39,824 --> 01:18:40,657
[Gabby] Fine.

1862
01:18:44,829 --> 01:18:46,096
I'm building something.

1863
01:18:47,531 --> 01:18:50,300
A community of people who
live together as equals,

1864
01:18:50,333 --> 01:18:53,503
treating each other with
love and respect voluntarily.

1865
01:18:53,537 --> 01:18:55,839
I don't want robots who do my
bidding because they have to.

1866
01:18:55,872 --> 01:18:59,174
I intend to live among my
people, not rule over them.

1867
01:19:00,442 --> 01:19:01,610
So the problem arises.

1868
01:19:03,013 --> 01:19:05,314
How do we make a
community of people

1869
01:19:05,347 --> 01:19:08,985
who are not forced to be happy,

1870
01:19:09,019 --> 01:19:10,252
but choose to?

1871
01:19:11,687 --> 01:19:12,989
By giving them choice.

1872
01:19:13,023 --> 01:19:15,025
Creating people
inside of a utopia

1873
01:19:16,960 --> 01:19:18,862
that have no choice
whether or not to be there,

1874
01:19:18,895 --> 01:19:20,361
who may not want to be there,

1875
01:19:20,395 --> 01:19:22,998
who can't be anything other
than peaceful and loving,

1876
01:19:23,032 --> 01:19:25,233
that's more of a
dystopia, isn't it?

1877
01:19:25,266 --> 01:19:26,869
How do you mean?

1878
01:19:26,902 --> 01:19:28,369
Which feels more real?

1879
01:19:28,403 --> 01:19:31,472
A mindless automaton who
is programmed to love you

1880
01:19:31,506 --> 01:19:33,008
or truly falling in
love with someone

1881
01:19:33,042 --> 01:19:35,510
as they genuinely
fall in love with you?

1882
01:19:36,644 --> 01:19:40,015
[chuckling] So that's
what this is about?

1883
01:19:40,049 --> 01:19:41,382
You want people to love you?

1884
01:19:41,416 --> 01:19:42,750
Yes.

1885
01:19:42,784 --> 01:19:46,386
And true love is
voluntary, not compulsory.

1886
01:19:46,420 --> 01:19:47,721
There has to be a
better way to have people

1887
01:19:47,754 --> 01:19:50,123
fall in love other than
throwing them into evil.

1888
01:19:50,157 --> 01:19:50,992
Is there?

1889
01:19:52,125 --> 01:19:53,861
I'm quite literally the
source of all things

1890
01:19:53,895 --> 01:19:56,530
you hold as good, all of it.

1891
01:19:56,563 --> 01:19:58,732
You're made in my image, yes?

1892
01:19:58,765 --> 01:20:00,601
So you're naturally inclined
to find joy and peace

1893
01:20:00,634 --> 01:20:02,235
in things like,

1894
01:20:02,269 --> 01:20:05,639
well, for starters,
joy and peace.

1895
01:20:07,107 --> 01:20:09,408
But I'm not looking for people
with Stockholm syndrome here.

1896
01:20:09,442 --> 01:20:11,310
If someone is going
to meaningfully choose

1897
01:20:11,344 --> 01:20:12,980
to spend their eternity with me,

1898
01:20:14,246 --> 01:20:15,983
they need to know what
the other option is.

1899
01:20:16,016 --> 01:20:18,351
And what is the
opposite of love?

1900
01:20:18,384 --> 01:20:19,518
Hatred.

1901
01:20:19,552 --> 01:20:20,353
Sure.

1902
01:20:21,387 --> 01:20:24,057
And the opposite
of joy, despair.

1903
01:20:24,091 --> 01:20:25,691
The opposite of all that is good

1904
01:20:26,860 --> 01:20:28,594
is all that is evil.

1905
01:20:30,129 --> 01:20:31,964
So I create my own adversary.

1906
01:20:33,298 --> 01:20:37,535
The physical personified
embodiment of all that I am not.

1907
01:20:40,672 --> 01:20:41,740
The devil.

1908
01:20:43,174 --> 01:20:44,643
If it helps you to think
of him that way, sure.

1909
01:20:44,676 --> 01:20:46,444
There's an actual devil?

1910
01:20:46,478 --> 01:20:48,981
Like a literal Satan?

1911
01:20:49,015 --> 01:20:50,515
The way you're imagining him

1912
01:20:50,548 --> 01:20:52,018
elevates him to a certain
status that he's never had.

1913
01:20:52,051 --> 01:20:54,185
He's less of some all
powerful enemy of humanity

1914
01:20:54,219 --> 01:20:58,589
and more of a really
strong perspective.

1915
01:20:58,622 --> 01:21:00,791
He's an existential
enemy more than anything.

1916
01:21:00,825 --> 01:21:02,259
Isn't he the one responsible

1917
01:21:02,292 --> 01:21:03,661
for all the awful shit
that happens in the world?

1918
01:21:03,694 --> 01:21:04,695
No.

1919
01:21:04,728 --> 01:21:05,562
You are.

1920
01:21:07,398 --> 01:21:10,567
That's a royal you there.

1921
01:21:10,601 --> 01:21:12,336
I'm whispering into
all of your ears.

1922
01:21:12,369 --> 01:21:13,771
And so as is The Adversary.

1923
01:21:13,805 --> 01:21:15,205
You make a choice of
which of those suggestions

1924
01:21:15,239 --> 01:21:16,908
align with your soul.

1925
01:21:16,941 --> 01:21:17,976
You're free to do so.

1926
01:21:19,375 --> 01:21:20,777
And having given you
that freedom on purpose,

1927
01:21:20,811 --> 01:21:23,446
I will respect the
choice you make with it.

1928
01:21:26,150 --> 01:21:28,052
You respect us so much
that you burn us in hell

1929
01:21:28,085 --> 01:21:30,453
when we make the wrong choice?

1930
01:21:30,486 --> 01:21:31,955
There has to be a better way.

1931
01:21:33,991 --> 01:21:35,591
Okay, here.

1932
01:21:35,625 --> 01:21:37,360
Let's say you're God, hmm?

1933
01:21:39,328 --> 01:21:40,864
What'd you do differently?

1934
01:21:40,898 --> 01:21:42,198
Easy.

1935
01:21:42,231 --> 01:21:43,866
Everybody goes to heaven.

1936
01:21:43,900 --> 01:21:44,700
Wow, everybody?

1937
01:21:44,733 --> 01:21:46,301
That's a bold move.

1938
01:21:46,334 --> 01:21:48,670
Some might accuse you
of eternal kidnapping.

1939
01:21:49,839 --> 01:21:51,841
Who wouldn't want
to go to heaven?

1940
01:21:51,874 --> 01:21:53,742
You've met people
who enjoy conflict.

1941
01:21:53,775 --> 01:21:55,111
Selfish people, violent people,

1942
01:21:55,144 --> 01:21:57,080
you think they're gonna
start singing kumbaya

1943
01:21:57,113 --> 01:21:58,081
because they're in paradise?

1944
01:21:58,114 --> 01:21:59,681
I don't know, maybe.

1945
01:21:59,715 --> 01:22:00,716
What if they don't?

1946
01:22:02,317 --> 01:22:04,252
Wouldn't they just turn
heaven back into earth,

1947
01:22:04,286 --> 01:22:06,688
good folks and bad folk
suffering together?

1948
01:22:06,722 --> 01:22:08,990
Okay, well, I would
give everyone a chance

1949
01:22:09,024 --> 01:22:10,859
and then kick them out if
they screwed up too much.

1950
01:22:10,892 --> 01:22:14,395
But in the meantime, they
can muck around in heaven.

1951
01:22:14,428 --> 01:22:16,664
Wouldn't that diminish paradise

1952
01:22:16,697 --> 01:22:18,632
for the good people
trying to enjoy it?

1953
01:22:20,102 --> 01:22:23,704
Can you see why you would
need a screening process,

1954
01:22:25,207 --> 01:22:27,008
perhaps a lifetime
to allow people

1955
01:22:27,042 --> 01:22:28,476
to sort themselves
into or out of it?

1956
01:22:28,509 --> 01:22:30,846
So that's what life is?

1957
01:22:30,879 --> 01:22:32,079
A screening process?

1958
01:22:33,246 --> 01:22:34,514
[The Lord] You can
think of it that way.

1959
01:22:34,547 --> 01:22:35,916
Okay, fine.

1960
01:22:35,950 --> 01:22:40,020
So a lifetime to
weed out the Hitlers

1961
01:22:40,054 --> 01:22:42,823
and the Jeffrey Dahmer's
I get that, but...

1962
01:22:42,857 --> 01:22:44,825
I mean I wouldn't do
this to people like me.

1963
01:22:44,859 --> 01:22:46,861
I'm a pretty good
person, generally.

1964
01:22:47,862 --> 01:22:48,695
Aren't I?

1965
01:22:51,132 --> 01:22:53,167
Depends on who you're
comparing yourself against.

1966
01:22:53,200 --> 01:22:55,136
Against Hitler or
Jeffrey Dahmer, sure.

1967
01:22:55,168 --> 01:22:58,370
But compared to my goodness,

1968
01:22:58,403 --> 01:23:01,507
compared to the goodness of
paradise, are you perfect?

1969
01:23:02,708 --> 01:23:04,777
If I told you you
had to earn heaven

1970
01:23:04,811 --> 01:23:07,213
how confident are you that
you actually deserve it?

1971
01:23:07,247 --> 01:23:08,181
[Gabby] Who can answer that?

1972
01:23:08,214 --> 01:23:09,048
I can.

1973
01:23:10,250 --> 01:23:11,750
And if you're saying
that you don't know

1974
01:23:11,784 --> 01:23:13,585
aren't you really telling
me that you can't be sure?

1975
01:23:13,619 --> 01:23:16,421
That you may have done some
things to void your ticket?

1976
01:23:16,455 --> 01:23:17,857
Okay, yeah.

1977
01:23:17,891 --> 01:23:19,590
But it's not like my worst
moments are all that I've done.

1978
01:23:19,624 --> 01:23:21,260
I've been the good
Samaritan too.

1979
01:23:21,292 --> 01:23:22,493
Yeah, but take out
all the good you've done

1980
01:23:22,527 --> 01:23:23,327
out of obligation,

1981
01:23:23,361 --> 01:23:24,797
wanting people to like you,

1982
01:23:24,830 --> 01:23:26,932
wanting to like yourself,

1983
01:23:26,965 --> 01:23:29,534
hoping for some sort of
reciprocation or reward.

1984
01:23:30,735 --> 01:23:32,370
How many moments
of genuine altruism

1985
01:23:32,403 --> 01:23:33,571
do you think you've
had in your life?

1986
01:23:33,604 --> 01:23:35,773
I don't know, dude,
but it isn't zero.

1987
01:23:37,542 --> 01:23:38,342
Is it?

1988
01:23:38,376 --> 01:23:39,845
No.

1989
01:23:39,878 --> 01:23:43,081
There've been some. [chuckling]

1990
01:23:43,114 --> 01:23:44,614
Then those should count.

1991
01:23:44,648 --> 01:23:46,349
If I'm the judge, then those
moments count for something.

1992
01:23:46,383 --> 01:23:48,518
Yeah, that'd be a strange
courtroom though, wouldn't it?

1993
01:23:48,552 --> 01:23:50,620
Would you offer John Wayne
Gacy a pardon for the murders

1994
01:23:50,654 --> 01:23:54,192
just because he brought joy
to children as a party clown?

1995
01:23:54,225 --> 01:23:55,392
[Gabby] No.

1996
01:23:55,425 --> 01:23:57,427
See, when you have
to pass judgment

1997
01:23:57,460 --> 01:23:59,831
on the evil someone's done,

1998
01:23:59,864 --> 01:24:01,631
the good they've
done is irrelevant.

1999
01:24:01,665 --> 01:24:02,566
Just seems cruel.

2000
01:24:02,599 --> 01:24:03,633
I'll tell you what.

2001
01:24:04,734 --> 01:24:07,636
If you got a better
idea, tell me.

2002
01:24:08,972 --> 01:24:10,773
What about karma?

2003
01:24:10,807 --> 01:24:11,707
So simple.

2004
01:24:11,740 --> 01:24:12,943
Why didn't I think of that?

2005
01:24:12,976 --> 01:24:14,177
What is that, like
a point system?

2006
01:24:14,211 --> 01:24:15,477
[Gabby] Why not?

2007
01:24:15,511 --> 01:24:17,013
You tell me.

2008
01:24:17,047 --> 01:24:18,414
What do you tell the person
who is one point away

2009
01:24:18,447 --> 01:24:19,883
from getting into heaven?

2010
01:24:19,916 --> 01:24:22,085
I'm so sorry, Ms. Fillmore.

2011
01:24:22,118 --> 01:24:23,485
If you did just picked
up your neighbor's kids

2012
01:24:23,519 --> 01:24:25,088
from soccer practice
one more time.

2013
01:24:25,121 --> 01:24:26,990
Well, eternal
damnation for you then.

2014
01:24:27,924 --> 01:24:29,358
Is that more fair?

2015
01:24:29,391 --> 01:24:30,894
I would make an exception.

2016
01:24:32,094 --> 01:24:34,163
What about the people
who are two points off?

2017
01:24:34,196 --> 01:24:35,030
Three?

2018
01:24:35,931 --> 01:24:36,999
We back to everybody gets in?

2019
01:24:37,032 --> 01:24:38,533
Okay, fine.

2020
01:24:38,566 --> 01:24:39,767
It's a firm line.

2021
01:24:39,802 --> 01:24:41,303
I get it, God has to
make tough decisions.

2022
01:24:41,337 --> 01:24:43,339
But fair is fair and
one point is one point.

2023
01:24:43,371 --> 01:24:46,574
Wow, that's very
bureaucratic of you.

2024
01:24:46,608 --> 01:24:47,877
Critics might call
you legalistic.

2025
01:24:47,910 --> 01:24:51,213
So now, what about the
guy who's done good

2026
01:24:51,247 --> 01:24:53,082
his entire life, right?

2027
01:24:53,115 --> 01:24:54,616
But molested a child
a couple of times.

2028
01:24:54,649 --> 01:24:55,984
I'm sure his karma score
would be pretty high.

2029
01:24:56,017 --> 01:24:57,218
You let him in?

2030
01:24:57,252 --> 01:24:58,619
Maybe especially
bad crimes have

2031
01:24:58,652 --> 01:25:01,455
a one strike and
you're out rule.

2032
01:25:01,488 --> 01:25:03,024
That's an idea, there you go.

2033
01:25:04,325 --> 01:25:06,261
What are these especially
bad crimes then?

2034
01:25:07,594 --> 01:25:10,430
You know, cold
blooded murder, rape.

2035
01:25:12,432 --> 01:25:13,600
Why those?

2036
01:25:13,634 --> 01:25:15,669
Because they make
you a bad human.

2037
01:25:15,702 --> 01:25:17,138
They destroy people.

2038
01:25:17,171 --> 01:25:18,572
Yeah but what about liars
and bullies and thieves?

2039
01:25:18,605 --> 01:25:19,538
Don't they hurt people?

2040
01:25:19,572 --> 01:25:21,308
They destroy people too, right?

2041
01:25:21,341 --> 01:25:23,343
I mean, yeah, but if you
did away with the murders

2042
01:25:23,377 --> 01:25:25,245
and the rapists, then
that's a good start, right?

2043
01:25:25,279 --> 01:25:26,479
Good start, yeah.

2044
01:25:26,512 --> 01:25:30,716
But an eternal paradise
is finished, isn't it?

2045
01:25:30,750 --> 01:25:31,985
When you imagine
yourself in a place

2046
01:25:32,019 --> 01:25:33,987
where you can have
your stuff stolen,

2047
01:25:34,021 --> 01:25:35,389
where you can't take
people at their word,

2048
01:25:35,421 --> 01:25:38,358
where you can be made
to feel bad or inferior,

2049
01:25:39,525 --> 01:25:41,929
are you imagining
yourself in heaven?

2050
01:25:41,962 --> 01:25:43,162
[Gabby] No.

2051
01:25:43,195 --> 01:25:44,096
There's the rub.

2052
01:25:45,231 --> 01:25:48,367
We want an eternal place
of perfect goodness.

2053
01:25:48,401 --> 01:25:51,770
Any bit of evil destroys
what we're working towards.

2054
01:25:51,804 --> 01:25:53,873
But that would mean
that telling a lie

2055
01:25:53,906 --> 01:25:55,473
and murder are equal.

2056
01:25:55,507 --> 01:25:56,741
I never said they were equal.

2057
01:25:56,775 --> 01:25:58,411
Think about a deck of cards.

2058
01:25:58,443 --> 01:26:00,880
Would did anybody say that a
King and a three are equal?

2059
01:26:00,913 --> 01:26:02,647
[Gabby] Of course not.

2060
01:26:02,681 --> 01:26:05,450
What happens if we
build a house of cards?

2061
01:26:05,483 --> 01:26:07,118
Any card removed from
that delicate tower

2062
01:26:07,152 --> 01:26:08,320
and it'll collapse.

2063
01:26:08,353 --> 01:26:10,388
It doesn't matter if
it's a King or a three.

2064
01:26:10,422 --> 01:26:11,856
This is just making
it sound impossible

2065
01:26:11,890 --> 01:26:13,624
to judge a person's
moral choices fairly.

2066
01:26:13,657 --> 01:26:15,260
Oh, it's possible.

2067
01:26:15,293 --> 01:26:17,896
It's just really bleak.

2068
01:26:17,929 --> 01:26:21,199
If I judged you all fairly,
no one would get in.

2069
01:26:21,232 --> 01:26:22,466
I'd be alone in paradise.

2070
01:26:22,499 --> 01:26:24,768
I may as well have
not created anything.

2071
01:26:24,803 --> 01:26:26,104
Trust me.

2072
01:26:26,137 --> 01:26:27,538
You don't want my fairness.

2073
01:26:29,808 --> 01:26:31,275
You want my mercy.

2074
01:26:35,813 --> 01:26:39,482
You said that life was
a screening process, yeah?

2075
01:26:39,515 --> 01:26:40,451
A test?

2076
01:26:40,483 --> 01:26:41,784
Mhmm, I did.

2077
01:26:41,819 --> 01:26:45,122
So then what's the
point if everyone fails?

2078
01:26:45,990 --> 01:26:47,724
What are you doing here?

2079
01:26:47,757 --> 01:26:49,793
If everyone is on
an equal playing field

2080
01:26:49,827 --> 01:26:53,831
of moral disqualification,
then maybe, maybe.

2081
01:26:53,864 --> 01:26:55,764
That's not the most
important part of deciding

2082
01:26:55,798 --> 01:26:57,200
who can get along in heaven.

2083
01:27:03,373 --> 01:27:04,740
It's not a moral test.

2084
01:27:04,773 --> 01:27:06,275
[chuckling] Bingo.

2085
01:27:07,944 --> 01:27:09,745
Okay, well then

2086
01:27:09,778 --> 01:27:11,447
what about all the people
who spend their lives

2087
01:27:11,481 --> 01:27:12,815
trying to be good?

2088
01:27:12,849 --> 01:27:14,083
It just doesn't matter.

2089
01:27:14,117 --> 01:27:16,752
Practically speaking,
it matters a great deal.

2090
01:27:16,785 --> 01:27:18,754
It makes the world
a better place.

2091
01:27:18,788 --> 01:27:21,522
But nobody chooses to be
that way 100% of the time

2092
01:27:21,555 --> 01:27:22,757
or for the right motives.

2093
01:27:22,791 --> 01:27:24,159
At least not in a way
that could allow someone

2094
01:27:24,192 --> 01:27:26,428
to earn heaven.

2095
01:27:27,496 --> 01:27:28,596
Even little things,

2096
01:27:29,998 --> 01:27:33,301
like hiding a smoking habit
come from a heart that deceives.

2097
01:27:33,335 --> 01:27:34,602
Wait, you know I smoke?

2098
01:27:35,669 --> 01:27:37,472
Does Michael know I smoke?

2099
01:27:37,506 --> 01:27:38,306
Nope.

2100
01:27:39,941 --> 01:27:41,810
Then why didn't
you just start there,

2101
01:27:41,843 --> 01:27:43,277
if you wanted me to believe
you this whole time?

2102
01:27:43,310 --> 01:27:45,813
You would have assumed Michael
smelled it on your clothes.

2103
01:27:45,846 --> 01:27:48,315
You trust me or doubt me first.

2104
01:27:49,517 --> 01:27:50,784
Then you block out
what doesn't fit.

2105
01:27:50,818 --> 01:27:52,253
That seems so petty, though.

2106
01:27:52,286 --> 01:27:54,654
I mean, I'm damned because
I'm not vocal about my vices?

2107
01:27:54,687 --> 01:27:56,290
That's just one small fruit

2108
01:27:56,323 --> 01:27:59,493
that grows in a heart
composed of evil soil.

2109
01:27:59,527 --> 01:28:00,861
One that serves itself,

2110
01:28:00,895 --> 01:28:05,032
not one that loves and
trusts others first.

2111
01:28:05,066 --> 01:28:06,566
I see what you would do

2112
01:28:06,599 --> 01:28:09,668
if this societal shackles of
law and order were let loose

2113
01:28:09,701 --> 01:28:12,238
and you could do anything
that you desired.

2114
01:28:12,272 --> 01:28:16,009
It's in everyone to some degree.

2115
01:28:16,042 --> 01:28:17,243
It doesn't really bode well

2116
01:28:17,277 --> 01:28:19,179
for what you would
do in paradise.

2117
01:28:19,212 --> 01:28:22,949
I need people that will
retain perfection voluntarily.

2118
01:28:24,918 --> 01:28:28,021
It's a blessing that
this isn't a moral test.

2119
01:28:29,422 --> 01:28:30,790
You let terrible evil
things happen to us,

2120
01:28:30,823 --> 01:28:32,991
and then you just take the ones

2121
01:28:33,025 --> 01:28:35,060
who suck up to you
into heaven, hmm?

2122
01:28:35,094 --> 01:28:36,495
[The Lord] Hmm.

2123
01:28:36,528 --> 01:28:37,728
That's some Job shit.

2124
01:28:39,098 --> 01:28:43,502
If anything, you're
all like Adam and Eve.

2125
01:28:44,369 --> 01:28:45,838
You remember them, don't you?

2126
01:28:45,871 --> 01:28:48,974
You damned all of humanity
because they ate an apple.

2127
01:28:49,007 --> 01:28:51,443
That's not exactly the
point of that illustration.

2128
01:28:51,477 --> 01:28:53,445
Do you have any more ideas on
how to restructure my universe

2129
01:28:53,479 --> 01:28:55,480
or you got time
for a quick story?

2130
01:28:57,081 --> 01:28:58,449
Go ahead.

2131
01:29:03,753 --> 01:29:05,156
I'm playing the long game.

2132
01:29:08,226 --> 01:29:10,461
In the beginning, I gave
humanity a prototype

2133
01:29:10,495 --> 01:29:11,529
for the paradise
that I'm building.

2134
01:29:11,562 --> 01:29:13,131
A world separate from mine,

2135
01:29:13,164 --> 01:29:14,932
where they could
do as they pleased

2136
01:29:14,966 --> 01:29:17,802
without destroying heaven.

2137
01:29:17,835 --> 01:29:19,735
So the question on the table is

2138
01:29:19,768 --> 01:29:21,071
how do I sort out those

2139
01:29:21,104 --> 01:29:23,607
who can get along
peacefully in heaven?

2140
01:29:23,639 --> 01:29:26,276
I gave them the bare
minimum required for a test.

2141
01:29:26,309 --> 01:29:28,512
Something they weren't
permitted to do,

2142
01:29:28,545 --> 01:29:29,813
but the freedom to do it.

2143
01:29:31,014 --> 01:29:32,382
The story you're familiar with,

2144
01:29:32,415 --> 01:29:34,650
the tree of the knowledge
of good and evil.

2145
01:29:34,683 --> 01:29:37,554
I set things up so that
eating from the tree

2146
01:29:37,587 --> 01:29:40,557
would allow humanity
to behave imperfectly.

2147
01:29:44,393 --> 01:29:47,062
It gave the choice
if a person chose it

2148
01:29:48,597 --> 01:29:50,665
to commit evil.

2149
01:29:50,698 --> 01:29:53,169
I explained to them
in no uncertain terms

2150
01:29:53,202 --> 01:29:54,970
that eating from the tree

2151
01:29:55,004 --> 01:29:58,607
would bring only
suffering, only death.

2152
01:29:58,641 --> 01:29:59,608
It wasn't a moral test,

2153
01:29:59,642 --> 01:30:01,776
since, well eating from the tree

2154
01:30:01,810 --> 01:30:03,279
would have awakened the capacity

2155
01:30:03,312 --> 01:30:05,247
for there to be morality
in the first place anyway.

2156
01:30:05,281 --> 01:30:08,715
It was a test of whether or
not my people trusted me.

2157
01:30:09,784 --> 01:30:11,819
[cork popping]

2158
01:30:11,853 --> 01:30:13,521
It could have been anything.

2159
01:30:13,555 --> 01:30:14,556
The point was,

2160
01:30:15,823 --> 01:30:18,426
if they trusted
me and no one ate,

2161
01:30:19,294 --> 01:30:21,296
no evil would enter the world.

2162
01:30:21,329 --> 01:30:22,163
No suffering.

2163
01:30:23,364 --> 01:30:24,765
Trust isn't trust
unless it is given

2164
01:30:24,799 --> 01:30:26,401
in spite of a reason to doubt.

2165
01:30:26,434 --> 01:30:29,037
So I gave The Adversary
a voice in the garden.

2166
01:30:30,605 --> 01:30:32,940
He told them I could be lying.

2167
01:30:32,973 --> 01:30:35,809
He said seek certainty
over trusting my word.

2168
01:30:37,477 --> 01:30:38,912
And that's what they did.

2169
01:30:38,946 --> 01:30:40,180
You'd hope it wouldn't
be the first people.

2170
01:30:40,214 --> 01:30:41,882
You know, maybe we get
a few generations in

2171
01:30:41,915 --> 01:30:43,383
before it all falls apart, but

2172
01:30:44,451 --> 01:30:47,354
right away, the cards collapsed.

2173
01:30:48,555 --> 01:30:51,191
And as a result, all
of their descendants,

2174
01:30:52,826 --> 01:30:53,627
you...

2175
01:30:54,927 --> 01:30:57,630
are imperfect and broken.

2176
01:30:59,999 --> 01:31:01,133
You can have paradise
back tomorrow

2177
01:31:01,167 --> 01:31:02,335
if you all collectively chose it

2178
01:31:02,368 --> 01:31:05,271
but there are none
among you who truly do.

2179
01:31:07,073 --> 01:31:08,773
You can all choose evil.

2180
01:31:09,875 --> 01:31:11,110
Hmm.

2181
01:31:11,143 --> 01:31:12,812
And at some point you
at least dip your toes

2182
01:31:12,845 --> 01:31:13,745
into its waters.

2183
01:31:15,147 --> 01:31:17,650
So what's left is this system

2184
01:31:17,683 --> 01:31:19,017
where you're faced
with the same decision

2185
01:31:19,050 --> 01:31:20,885
that the first people once had.

2186
01:31:21,853 --> 01:31:23,388
Do you trust the voice of faith

2187
01:31:26,491 --> 01:31:27,692
or the voice of doubt?

2188
01:31:27,726 --> 01:31:29,561
It still doesn't seem fair.

2189
01:31:29,594 --> 01:31:31,496
I mean, Adam and Eve
didn't have to guess

2190
01:31:31,529 --> 01:31:33,798
whether or not you even existed.

2191
01:31:33,832 --> 01:31:35,967
It clearly didn't
help, did it?

2192
01:31:36,001 --> 01:31:37,302
They still ate.

2193
01:31:37,335 --> 01:31:38,536
The test remains the same,

2194
01:31:38,570 --> 01:31:40,672
as long as there are
equal voices of trust

2195
01:31:42,140 --> 01:31:42,973
and doubt.

2196
01:31:46,277 --> 01:31:47,077
Okay.

2197
01:31:50,414 --> 01:31:51,348
I'll bite.

2198
01:31:51,382 --> 01:31:52,349
Unfortunate choice of words.

2199
01:31:52,383 --> 01:31:53,484
I meant figuratively.

2200
01:31:53,517 --> 01:31:54,985
Ah, carry on then.

2201
01:31:56,453 --> 01:32:00,724
So you take the ones who
trust you into paradise.

2202
01:32:00,758 --> 01:32:01,458
Yup.

2203
01:32:01,492 --> 01:32:02,793
I get that.

2204
01:32:02,826 --> 01:32:04,795
But if we're all evil anyway

2205
01:32:04,828 --> 01:32:06,563
how come we don't just
fuck heaven right back up

2206
01:32:06,596 --> 01:32:08,097
once we get there?

2207
01:32:08,131 --> 01:32:10,867
I restore your shattered
perfection after you die.

2208
01:32:10,900 --> 01:32:13,036
I give you the same choice
the first people once had,

2209
01:32:13,069 --> 01:32:16,873
to choose to be perfect.

2210
01:32:16,906 --> 01:32:18,741
By making up heaven of
those people who trust me

2211
01:32:18,776 --> 01:32:22,645
I've decided for the ones who
wouldn't eat from the tree.

2212
01:32:24,147 --> 01:32:26,516
People who will keep within
the boundaries of goodness

2213
01:32:26,549 --> 01:32:28,786
that I've set because,

2214
01:32:28,818 --> 01:32:30,086
well, because they
trust me when I say

2215
01:32:30,119 --> 01:32:32,621
certain things will
only unleash suffering.

2216
01:32:34,122 --> 01:32:37,025
The rules aren't just there
so I can exert my authority.

2217
01:32:38,927 --> 01:32:40,028
Okay, fine.

2218
01:32:40,062 --> 01:32:44,166
So you get your perfect
kingdom one day.

2219
01:32:46,168 --> 01:32:47,869
But in the meantime it's pain.

2220
01:32:49,171 --> 01:32:51,306
You make us look into
the face of evil.

2221
01:32:52,374 --> 01:32:55,609
You watch us starve,

2222
01:32:55,643 --> 01:32:59,080
and contract disease,
die violent deaths.

2223
01:33:00,247 --> 01:33:02,016
And yet you continue
to put us here.

2224
01:33:03,484 --> 01:33:04,719
And then at the end of it

2225
01:33:04,752 --> 01:33:06,087
not even everyone
gets into heaven.

2226
01:33:07,455 --> 01:33:12,326
So no matter your reasoning,
you gave us suffering.

2227
01:33:13,494 --> 01:33:14,695
How does that not
make you a monster?

2228
01:33:16,130 --> 01:33:17,598
If your child has leukemia,

2229
01:33:18,998 --> 01:33:21,968
are you a monster for putting
them through chemotherapy?

2230
01:33:22,001 --> 01:33:22,837
Is the doctor?

2231
01:33:25,840 --> 01:33:27,173
No.

2232
01:33:27,207 --> 01:33:29,042
What if there isn't
a 100% success rate

2233
01:33:29,075 --> 01:33:30,577
in healing them?

2234
01:33:30,610 --> 01:33:31,745
Then are they monsters?

2235
01:33:34,114 --> 01:33:35,515
No.

2236
01:33:35,548 --> 01:33:38,051
So sometimes, sometimes,

2237
01:33:39,452 --> 01:33:42,654
is suffering necessary to get
from unhealthy to healthy?

2238
01:33:42,688 --> 01:33:44,256
Do you sometimes have
to subject yourself

2239
01:33:44,289 --> 01:33:47,326
or someone that you love
to temporary suffering

2240
01:33:47,359 --> 01:33:49,561
maybe only on the
hope of a chance

2241
01:33:49,595 --> 01:33:50,929
at a long-term benefit?

2242
01:33:52,464 --> 01:33:53,298
Maybe.

2243
01:33:55,267 --> 01:33:56,068
Yeah.

2244
01:33:56,101 --> 01:33:56,935
Mhmm.

2245
01:33:58,170 --> 01:33:59,806
Okay, but then

2246
01:33:59,839 --> 01:34:02,608
what about things
like earthquakes

2247
01:34:02,641 --> 01:34:04,811
and wildfires and hurricanes?

2248
01:34:05,944 --> 01:34:07,979
You're going to pin
that on human morality?

2249
01:34:09,113 --> 01:34:10,014
Are you grieving
that the world

2250
01:34:10,047 --> 01:34:11,349
isn't as it's supposed to be?

2251
01:34:12,283 --> 01:34:13,117
Me too.

2252
01:34:14,419 --> 01:34:17,588
We both know that
perfection is the standard.

2253
01:34:17,622 --> 01:34:19,957
We're offended when that's
violated, aren't we?

2254
01:34:22,326 --> 01:34:24,595
When humanity decided to
cut itself off from me,

2255
01:34:24,629 --> 01:34:26,865
I stopped micromanaging
your world.

2256
01:34:26,899 --> 01:34:28,533
Without my divine nature,

2257
01:34:30,401 --> 01:34:32,002
natural processes can do damage.

2258
01:34:33,203 --> 01:34:34,806
Can't always be 72
degrees and sunny.

2259
01:34:36,540 --> 01:34:39,709
A pot abandoned on the
stove will boil over.

2260
01:34:40,845 --> 01:34:42,479
The echoes of shattered
perfection are loud,

2261
01:34:42,512 --> 01:34:45,148
but you can only grieve
for a rod bent out of shape

2262
01:34:45,182 --> 01:34:47,885
if somewhere in you, you
know it ought to be straight.

2263
01:34:50,320 --> 01:34:51,955
We can talk about
this all night.

2264
01:34:53,290 --> 01:34:54,623
We can talk about
everything that I've done,

2265
01:34:54,657 --> 01:34:55,926
am doing, and will do.

2266
01:34:55,991 --> 01:34:57,660
You can analyze
it tirelessly, but

2267
01:34:59,028 --> 01:35:00,996
that would be making a decision
based upon your judgment.

2268
01:35:01,030 --> 01:35:02,498
And in all honesty,

2269
01:35:02,531 --> 01:35:05,668
I'm not worried about what
your judgment call is here.

2270
01:35:05,701 --> 01:35:08,204
You don't really have the
perspective to make one.

2271
01:35:10,072 --> 01:35:11,307
What I'm wondering is,

2272
01:35:12,308 --> 01:35:14,143
do you trust me?

2273
01:35:15,377 --> 01:35:16,378
How can I?

2274
01:35:17,814 --> 01:35:20,883
How can I trust a person and
a plan with so much darkness?

2275
01:35:20,916 --> 01:35:22,083
The same way that
a mother trusts

2276
01:35:22,116 --> 01:35:23,751
that the pain of childbirth

2277
01:35:23,786 --> 01:35:26,120
is worth the bringing
in of new life.

2278
01:35:26,154 --> 01:35:28,723
I cannot build this
without labor pains.

2279
01:35:28,756 --> 01:35:31,092
But I've determined that this
is the best possible scenario

2280
01:35:31,125 --> 01:35:34,195
to craft the best
possible reality.

2281
01:35:34,229 --> 01:35:37,098
Okay but why does the
best possible reality

2282
01:35:37,131 --> 01:35:38,500
have to have a hell in it?

2283
01:35:40,903 --> 01:35:41,937
Yours wouldn't huh?

2284
01:35:41,971 --> 01:35:42,804
No.

2285
01:35:43,972 --> 01:35:45,405
I couldn't torture
people for eternity

2286
01:35:45,439 --> 01:35:47,775
and then feel like I had
the moral high ground.

2287
01:35:49,811 --> 01:35:52,679
I am the source
of all that is good.

2288
01:35:52,713 --> 01:35:54,715
When someone decides
they don't want me,

2289
01:35:56,049 --> 01:35:58,018
I give their eternal soul

2290
01:35:58,051 --> 01:36:00,487
its own place after
death without me

2291
01:36:00,521 --> 01:36:01,421
as they've desired.

2292
01:36:02,891 --> 01:36:06,459
What do you think a place
devoid of all goodness is like?

2293
01:36:06,492 --> 01:36:07,326
Torture.

2294
01:36:11,932 --> 01:36:13,199
Hell.

2295
01:36:13,232 --> 01:36:14,066
Exactly.

2296
01:36:15,735 --> 01:36:18,337
I didn't make hell
to torture people in.

2297
01:36:20,640 --> 01:36:23,109
People become hell.

2298
01:36:24,945 --> 01:36:27,647
And I give them their own
domain separate from heaven.

2299
01:36:29,715 --> 01:36:31,483
They reject the antidote
for the suffering

2300
01:36:31,516 --> 01:36:32,684
in their own heart

2301
01:36:32,717 --> 01:36:34,219
and choose to live
in that for eternity.

2302
01:36:36,187 --> 01:36:38,690
I don't torture people in hell.

2303
01:36:38,723 --> 01:36:40,993
You don't blame a warm fire
for the coldness of the people

2304
01:36:41,027 --> 01:36:42,627
who choose not to sit beside it.

2305
01:36:45,630 --> 01:36:47,299
I'm trying to process this.

2306
01:36:47,332 --> 01:36:48,633
It's a hell of a lot to take in.

2307
01:36:48,667 --> 01:36:51,403
I'd advise you not
to take your time.

2308
01:36:51,436 --> 01:36:53,138
Tomorrow only grows closer.

2309
01:36:54,338 --> 01:36:55,840
Yeah, okay.

2310
01:36:55,874 --> 01:36:59,510
It's just a lot of pressure.

2311
01:36:59,543 --> 01:37:02,981
I need to wrap my brain
around everything.

2312
01:37:05,082 --> 01:37:05,917
Gabrielle.

2313
01:37:07,084 --> 01:37:11,288
Do you trust with your
brain or your heart?

2314
01:37:11,322 --> 01:37:13,591
[gentle music]

2315
01:37:13,624 --> 01:37:15,060
If you'd grasp that,

2316
01:37:15,092 --> 01:37:16,928
maybe your clock wouldn't
be ticking so loudly.

2317
01:37:38,514 --> 01:37:41,217
I love you, Gabrielle.

2318
01:37:58,101 --> 01:37:58,935
Hmm?

2319
01:38:00,435 --> 01:38:01,236
I know, I just,

2320
01:38:02,170 --> 01:38:03,705
I think that I do.

2321
01:38:03,739 --> 01:38:05,875
It's just a lot
for me to say it.

2322
01:38:08,010 --> 01:38:08,844
Huh?

2323
01:38:09,811 --> 01:38:11,245
What do you mean?

2324
01:38:12,814 --> 01:38:13,915
What do you mean?

2325
01:38:13,949 --> 01:38:16,617
I asked if you like the wine.

